description: TEHRAN - In an analysis, the Iran newspaper discussed the importance of President Masoud Pezeshkian's speech at the UN General Assembly.
title: Iran overcomes challenges with authority

description: TEHRAN- Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu attempted to whitewash the regime’s atrocious crimes in Gaza and Lebanon as he delivered a speech at the United Nations General Assembly in New York amid large protests against his trip to the United States.
title: Netanyahu's smoke and mirrors

description: TEHRAN -The Iranian Foreign Ministry issued a statement describing the Israeli massive air strikes on the south of the Lebanese capital Beirut with American-supplied weapons as an open violation of international law and a violation of the Lebanese national sovereignty.
title: Iran holds US complicit in Israeli massive air attacks on Beirut

description: TEHRAN – Iranian Foreign Minister Abbas Araqchi has held a series of high-profile meetings with global leaders and foreign ministers on the sidelines of the 79th session of the United Nations General Assembly (UNGA) in New York, strengthening bilateral relations and discussing key regional and international issues.
title: Araqchi highlights enhancing bilateral ties in high-level talks on UNGA sidelines

description: TEHRAN- Iranian Foreign Minister Abbas Araqchi extended his congratulations to Armenian Foreign Minister Ararat Mirzoyan on the occasion of Armenia's National Day anniversary.
title: Iranian FM congratulates Armenian counterpart on National Day

description: TEHRAN – Iranian Foreign Minister Abbas Araqchi has emphasized that peace and security in the region can only be achieved by ending the Israeli occupation of Palestinian territories and restoring the Palestinian people’s fundamental rights, including the right to self-determination.
title: Ending Israeli occupation only way to achieve peace in region: Iran FM

description: TEHRAN- Senior border officials from Iran and Qatar have engaged in discussions aimed at enhancing border cooperation between their nations.
title: Iran, Qatar security officials hold talks to boost border cooperation

description: TEHRAN – The Iranian President offered individual messages of congratulations to Turkmenistan's national leader and head of the People's Council, as well as the country's president, on the occasion of the anniversary of Turkmenistan's Independence Day.
title: Pezeshkian offers congratulations to Turkmen officials on Independence Day

description: TEHRAN – Masoud Pezeshkian, the president of Iran, is set to visit Qatar to take part in the upcoming Asia Cooperation Dialogue (ACD) Summit.
title: Iranian president to attend Asia Cooperation Dialogue Summit in Qatar

description: MADRID – Iranian President Masoud Pezeshkian made his debut at the United Nations General Assembly with a powerful speech addressing the Israel-Palestine conflict, condemning the atrocities committed against the people of Gaza.
title: Iranian president debut UNGA speech: a call for ‘honest dialogue’

description: TEHRAN – Iranian Foreign Ministry Spokesman Nasser Kanaani has upbraided U.S. politicians on social media for approving a new aid package to Israel, while the regime continues to pummel Gaza and escalate attacks against Lebanon.
title: Tehran censures U.S. for new aid package to Israel

description: TEHRAN - Following Friday prayers, worshippers in Tehran, along with participants across Iran, took part in nationwide rallies to denounce the Israeli regime's actions in Gaza and Lebanon.
title: Iranians hold nationwide rallies to condemn Israeli actions in Gaza, Lebanon

description: TEHRAN – Major General Hossein Salami, Chief Commander of the Islamic Revolution Guard Corps (IRGC), has predicted an imminent "amazing victory" for the Palestinian people who have been resolutely resisting Israel in the past 11 months.
title: Palestinian people poised for "amazing victory," IRGC chief declares

description: TEHRAN – Iran's Deputy Foreign Minister for Legal and International Affairs, Kazem Gharibabadi, delivered a scathing critique of the international community's failure to achieve nuclear disarmament, specifically targeting Israel's nuclear weapons program during a speech at the UN General Assembly's High-Level Plenary Meeting on the International Day for the Total Elimination of Nuclear Weapons.
title: Iran demands action against Israel's nuclear arsenal, insists ‘Israel must join NTP’

description: TEHRAN-October 12 is named National Hafez Day in the Persian calendar. It is a day in which the great Persian poet Hafez is honored in Iran. Every year Hafez Commemoration Week is held during the week leading to Hafez Day. However, “this year, due to the various programs planned for the event, the 28th Hafez Commemoration Week begin sooner on September 27,” said the director general of Department of Culture and Islamic Guidance in Fars Province on Tuesday.
title: Artistic performances, academic discussions planned for 28th Hafez commemoration week

description: TEHRAN – Iran and China have agreed to establish joint commissions to enhance economic, security, political, and cultural cooperation and operationalize the existing agreements, Iranian President Masoud Pezeshkian announced upon returning to Tehran from a three-day visit to the UN headquarters in New York.
title: Iran, China to deepen ties with new joint commissions

description: TEHRAN – In a message marking Sacred Defense Week, Leader of the Islamic Revolution Ayatollah Seyyed Ali Khamenei emphasized the importance of remembering the country's martyrs, calling it a guarantee for safeguarding the path of the Iranian nation and staying true to the ideals of the Islamic Revolution.
title: Leader issues message to commemorate Sacred Defense Week

description: TEHRAN-The Persian translation of the novel “Memorial Drive: A Daughter's Memoir” written by Natasha Trethewey has been released in the Iranian book market.
title: Natasha Trethewey’s “Memorial Drive: A Daughter's Memoir” published in Persian

description: TEHRAN - The Lebanese Civil Defense announced on Friday that 14 bodies and 6 injured people have been recovered following Israeli airstrikes on several areas.
title: Hezbollah shows no sign of backing down

description: TEHRAN – In a stark condemnation of the Israeli government's policies, Moody's Investors Service, a global credit rating agency, has downgraded Israel's sovereign credit rating, sending shockwaves through its financial landscape. This move, driven by concerns over the deepening political and economic instability fueled by the government's aggressive actions, has raised serious alarm bells about the uture of the Israeli economy.
title: Behind closed doors: Israel scrambling to avert another economic crisis

description: Israeli fighter jets launched a series of massive airstrikes on a crowded area in the Lebanese capital Beirut on Friday, causing widespread destruction with fears of a large death toll.
title: Barbaric attack on Beirut ordered from New York

description: Israeli fighter jets launched a series of massive airstrikes on a crowded area in the Lebanese capital Beirut on Friday, causing widespread destruction with fears of a large death toll.
title: Israel launches massive air raid on southern Beirut

description:
A collection of paintings by a group of artists including Ehsan Zia, Shokoufeh Karimi, Navid Bijani, Mohammadreza Shirvani and Mehdi Dashti is on view in an exhibition at the Iranian Artists Forum (IAF).
The exhibit will run until October 4 at the IAF that can be found at the Artists Park on North Mousavi Street, Taleqani Street.
title: What’s in Tehran art galleries

description: TEHRAN- Over 2,300 foreign documentaries from 123 countries have applied to participate in the 18th edition of Iran International Documentary Film Festival Cinéma Vérité, the organizers have announced.
title: Cinéma Vérité sees participation from 123 countries

description: TEHRAN – Tehran mayor Alireza Zakani has unveiled a tourism atlas, which is a guide dedicated to showcasing the rich cultural heritage and tourism attractions of the city’s historic core, roughly corresponding to District 12.
title: Tehran mayor unveils atlas showcasing cultural heritage of the city’s heart

description: TEHRAN - Iran has the potential to generate €6 billion annually from medical tourism with proper planning, according to Mohammad-Reza Vaez-Mahdavi, Chairman of Iran’s Scientific Association of Health Economy.
title: Iran could boost medical tourism revenues to €6 billion annually, says health official

description: Tehran – Iran’s Minister of Cultural Heritage, Tourism, and Handicrafts, Seyyed Reza Salehi-Amiri in a meeting with Georgia’s Minister of Culture, emphasized strengthening cooperation between the two nations in the fields of archaeology, restoration of artifacts, and exhibition activities.
title: Tehran, Tbilisi to enhance cooperation in archaeology and restoration

description: As we celebrate World Tourism Day 2024 under the theme “Tourism and Peace,” it is crucial to reflect on the profound role that the sector plays not only in economic development but also in promoting peace, mutual understanding, and reconciliation among nations.
title: Tourism as a bridge to peace and understanding

description: TEHRAN – On Thursday, 1100 Achaemenid-era clay tablets were returned to Iran from the United States, marking the sixth batch of such historical artifacts brought back to the ancient country.
title: Souvenir of New York: 1100 Achaemenid clay tablets returned home

description: TEHRAN – Iranian Energy Ministry plans to increase the country’s power generation capacity by 5,333 megawatts (MW) by the end of the current Iranian calendar year (late March 2025).
title: Nominal electricity generation capacity to rise 5,333MW by next Mar.

description: TEHRAN – Iran exported 4,856 tons of tea valued at $6.555 million in the first five months of the current Iranian calendar year (March 20-August 21), according to Mohammad Sadegh Hassani, the executive director of Iran’s Tea Syndicate.
title: Iranian tea export tops $6.5m in 5 months

description: TEHRAN - At the meeting of the BRICS energy ministers in Moscow, Iran's Energy Minister has proposed the development of cooperation among the member countries of this group, including the connection of the power grid of Russia, the Islamic Republic of Iran, the United Arab Emirates, and Saudi Arabia.
title: Iran proposes connecting power grid to Russia, UAE, Saudi Arabia

description: TEHRAN – Senior energy officials of Iran and Tajikistan have stressed their willingness to expand energy ties between the two countries, Shana reported.
title: Iran, Tajikistan underline boosting energy cooperation

description: TEHRAN- The value of Iran’s non-oil exports increased by 6.5 percent during the first six months of the current Iranian calendar year (March 20-September 21), as compared to the same period of time in the past year, the head of the Islamic Republic of Iran Customs Administration (IRICA) announced.
title: Iran’s non-oil export up over 6% in 6 months on year

description: TEHRAN- During a conference titled Iran Investment Opportunities, which was held prior to Iran Invest Expo, it was stated that 30 countries have announced their readiness to invest in Iran.
title: 30 countries announce readiness to invest in Iran

description: TEHRAN – Iran defeated India 1-0 in the 2025 AFC U20 Asian Cup China qualification on Friday.
title: Iran edge India in 2025 AFC U20 Asian Cup China qualifier

description: TEHRAN –A total of 193 cases of dengue fever have been diagnosed in the country, the deputy health minister has said.
title: Over 190 dengue fever cases reported

description: TEHRAN –The Iranian Red Crescent Society (IRCS) has held a training of trainers (TOT) workshop based on the United Nations Children’s Fund (UNICEF) training package on ‘Disability Inclusion for Frontline Workers’.
title: IRCS hosts TOT workshop on Disability Inclusion for Frontline Workers

description: TEHRAN –The World Food Program (WFP) has released a report, expounding on activities in Iran over the month of August.
title: WFP releases August report on Iran

description: Yemen’s Ansarullah has fired a missile at areas near Tel Aviv, the capital of Israel, in solidarity with the Lebanese.
title: Yemen fires missile at Tel Aviv in solidarity with Lebanon

description: Discussion around the topic of rabies is almost exclusively related to the dangers it poses to humans from dog bites. And it’s no wonder, because if a rabid bite is left untreated it is almost always fatal. Indeed, human deaths from rabies – almost always caused by dog bites – account for an estimated 59,000 fatalities each year.
title: By 2030 we must eliminate rabies in Asia and the Pacific

description: Israel dismisses global calls for a ceasefire with Hezbollah and continues a bombing campaign in Lebanon that has far killed more than 700 people since Monday, September 23.
title: Israeli strikes have killed 700 in Lebanon since Monday

description: TEHRAN - Vietnam’s Duc Giang Chemical swept Iran’s Saipa Club 3-0 (25-16, 25-11, 27-25) in the 5th-8th semifinals of the 2024 Asian Women’s Club Volleyball Championship at Chartchai Hall.
title: Duc Giang defeat Saipa in 2024 Asian Women’s Club Volleyball Championship
